HEADWORD: Cancroid
<hw>Can"croid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Cancer</ets> +
<ets>oid</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Resembling a
crab; pertaining to the <fam>Cancroidea</fam>, one of the families of
crabs, including the genus <gen>Cancer</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Like a cancer; <as>as, a <ex>cancroid</ex>
tumor</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cand</ent>⟦br⟧
